      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>You create an enervating ray of magic. You must make a ranged attack against your opponent’s EAC. On a hit, the target is immediately @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.33ynSbmexuxC3cAQ]{Exhausted} for the spell’s duration. A creature that succeeds at a Fortitude saving throw is only fatigued, unless it is already fatigued, in which case it instead becomes @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.33ynSbmexuxC3cAQ]{Exhausted} despite the saving throw.</p>\n<p>This spell has no effect on a creature that is already @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.33ynSbmexuxC3cAQ]{Exhausted}. Unlike normal exhaustion or fatigue, the effect ends as soon as the spell’s duration expires.</p>"
